# Health

Show repo-local integrity and repairability findings; with `--governance`, show
governance diagnostics for the active or selected change.

## Invocation
```bash
slipway health --json
slipway health --governance --json --change <slug>
slipway health --doctor --json
```

## Contract
- Read-only. Surfaces integrity findings, repairability, and (with `--governance`)
  governance signal provenance and required actions.
- `--doctor` synthesizes prioritized repair and recovery actions without mutating state.
- Suggest `slipway repair` only for findings it marks repairable.

## Flags
- `--json`: JSON output
- `--governance`: governance diagnostics for the active or selected change
- `--all`: show both repo health and governance health
- `--observations`: include detailed governance signal provenance
- `--doctor`: synthesize prioritized repair/recovery actions (no mutation)
- `--focus <alias>`: health focus override, e.g. `incident` (see `--list-focuses`)
- `--list-focuses`: list public health focuses
- `--format <text|json>`: output format for `--list-focuses`
- `--hydrate` / `--hydrate-ref <skill-id>/<name>`: append/restrict hydrate reference bodies (text output only)
- `--change <slug>`: target a specific change for governance health
{{- end -}}
